pageContext.claim: “We're just getting the numbers. And it looks like we won that big. And he's been a tremendous candidate, Mike Garcia. He went out. He worked, and he won, and he took back a seat from the Democrats in California. Think of that. In an area that nobody thought possible.”
pageContext.analysis: Republicans had held this California congressional seat until 2019. Democrats were not expected to lose it, but then, expectations suddenly changed. Katie Hill, the Democrat who flipped the district in 2018, resigned in scandal months after joining Congress.
